80,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-09-17T06:22:46.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>另外，香港前途關注組在其facebook指已去信英國愛丁堡大學學生會，就該校候任校長馬斐森，昨聯署譴責港獨言論表達不滿。<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n識玩</blockquote><br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1f8b86069a0bd77c22d721ed1b69504a846f7365","tid":403244,"uid":66436,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-09-17T06:24:53.000Z","msg":"poly同中大呢"},{"pid":"8396f4d20fb19cfbb92a114db1450fd8fe5333ee","tid":403244,"uid":47359,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-09-17T06:29:55.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>poly同中大呢</blockquote><br />\npoly冇su<br />\ncu咪有囉盲亨"},{"pid":"6166b214af4c823c271b72a03fa45f658da8357d","tid":403244,"uid":25164,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-09-17T06:34:02.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"3ba5a32456579ce6de79335a261b6c8fa4061f91","tid":403244,"uid":25164,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-09-17T06:37:05.000Z","msg":"btw 出返條link<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CUHK.SU/posts/1590570134338723\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FCUHK.SU%2Fposts%2F1590570134338723&d=uGz%2BZe8KJa%2FUzvndc0x6s57TfgnX9jywtYe9GXZmhCU%3D&h=7ba26c60\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/CUHK.SU/posts/1590570134338723</a><br />\n<br />\n【大專學界就大學校長聲明之回應 |  Response from Students&rsquo; Unions of Higher Institutions towards the Joint Statement by Heads of Universities】<br />\n<br />\n(Please scroll down for English version.)<br />\n<br />\n我們珍惜言論自由，此權利生而有之。校方不支持港獨，但大學師生享有言論自由，討論港獨絕無不可。所有下列的學生會，特此聲明，討論港獨絕對符合《基本法》第二十七條，校方請停止混淆視聽。<br />\n<br />\n香港城巿大學學生會<br />\n恒生管理學院學生會<br />\n香港浸會大學學生會<br />\n香港科技大學學生會<br />\n嶺南大學學生會<br />\n香港珠海學院學生會<br />\n香港高等教育科技學院學生會<br />\n香港教育大學學生會<br />\n香港大學學生會<br />\n香港公開大學學生會<br />\n香港樹仁大學學生會<br />\n香港中文大學學生會<br />\n<br />\nWe treasure freedom of expression, which is the right that we are born with. The universities do not support Hong Kong independence, but teachers and students still enjoy the freedom of speech to discuss Hong Kong independence. All students&rsquo; unions undersigned agree that discussion on Hong Kong independence is protected under Article 27 of the Basic Law. We urge the universities to stop misleading the public. <br />\n<br />\nCity University of Hong Kong Students&rsquo; Union<br />\nHang Seng Management College Students' Union<br />\nHong Kong Baptist University Students&rsquo; Union<br />\nHong Kong University of Science and Technology Students&rsquo; Union<br />\nLingnan University Students&rsquo; Union<br />\nStudent Union of Chu Hai College of Higher Education<br />\nTechnological and Higher Education Institute of Hong Kong Students&rsquo; Union<br />\nThe Education University of Hong Kong Students&rsquo; Union<br />\nThe Hong Kong University Students&rsquo; Union<br />\nThe Open University of Hong Kong Students&rsquo; Union<br />\nThe Student Union of Hong Kong Shue Yan University<br />\nThe Student Union of The Chinese University of Hong Kong"}]}